 :tx/rationale "Create task: ACP-2: Implement ActivationStrategy enum and strategy_for_k_eff() selector (ADR-BUDGET-007, INV-BUDGET-004). BACKGROUND: Four activation strategies for four k* regimes: Demonstrate (k*>0.7, full context ~300 tokens), Navigate (0.4-0.7, precise pointers ~100 tokens), Imperative (0.2-0.4, action only ~20 tokens), Signal (k*<0.2, harvest ~5 tokens). The strategy maps to the projection pyramid but is cognitively grounded: Demonstrate seeds the trajectory at session start, Navigate keeps the agent on-basin during active work, Imperative is the minimum viable activation when context is scarce, Signal is the harvest emergency. The selector function: strategy_for_k_eff(k_eff: f64) -> ActivationStrategy. Each strategy has a max_context_tokens() method returning the token budget for context filling. This replaces the current AttentionProfile ceiling mechanism — instead of per-command ceilings, the k*-adaptive strategy determines how much context is included. APPROACH: Add ActivationStrategy enum to budget.rs with Demonstrate/Navigate/Imperative/Signal variants. Each has max_context_tokens(). strategy_for_k_eff() uses the thresholds from INV-BUDGET-004. Tests: (A) k_eff=1.0 -> Demonstrate. (B) k_eff=0.5 -> Navigate. (C) k_eff=0.3 -> Imperative. (D) k_eff=0.1 -> Signal. (E) max_context_tokens is monotonically decreasing across strategies. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/budget.rs"
